<h2>Data Deletion Request</h2>
<p>If you wish to <strong>delete</strong> your personal data from Sakhi App, you can follow the steps below:</p>

<h3>1. How to Request Data Deletion:</h3>
<p>You can send a request for data deletion to our support email at <strong>[your contact email]</strong>. Please include the following details in your request:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Subject: <strong>Data Deletion Request</strong></li>
  <li>Full Name (as registered in the app)</li>
  <li>Email Address (associated with the app account)</li>
</ul>

<h3>2. What Happens After the Request:</h3>
<p>Once we receive your request, we will:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Verify your identity (to ensure that we are deleting data for the correct user).</li>
  <li>Delete your personal data from our systems, including any information stored within the app.</li>
  <li>Notify you once the deletion is complete.</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Data Deletion Timeline:</h3>
<p>Your data will be deleted within <strong>30 days</strong> of receiving your request. After deletion, your account and associated data will no longer be retrievable.</p>

<h3>4. Exceptions:</h3>
<p>We may retain certain data if it is required for legal or compliance reasons, or if you have ongoing transactions within the app. In such cases, we will inform you of the reason for retention.</p>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> Deleting your data may cause you to lose access to certain services and features within the app. It also does not affect any data that has already been shared with third parties.</p>
